text:
Fatemeh Rahbar (‎; 1964 – 7 March 2020) was an Iranian politician. She served as a member of the Islamic Consultative Assembly from 2004 to 2016. She died before retaking office in 2020. Rahbar was born in Tehran.
On 7 March 2020, Rahbar died in Tehran due to COVID-19 during the 2019–20 coronavirus pandemic. She was 56.
